        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 5 at 7:30PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 728 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 24 miles east of Winifred to 11 miles
northeast of Roy to 16 miles south of Lewistown. Movement was east
at 40 mph. In addition to lightning and brief heavy rainfall, wind
gusts in excess of 50 mph have been observed with this storm with
hail up to one half inch in diameter also possible as these storms
continue east across Fergus county.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Grass Range, Forestgrove, and Fred Robinson Bridge.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
